Spring Data — The Umbrella Project:
Spring Data is the parent project that provides a consistent, unified programming model for data access across different data stores:
        Spring Data (Umbrella):
        ├── Spring Data JPA          → Relational DBs (MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle)
        ├── Spring Data MongoDB      → MongoDB (NoSQL Document Store)
        ├── Spring Data Redis        → Redis (Key-Value Cache)
        ├── Spring Data Elasticsearch → Elasticsearch
        ├── Spring Data Cassandra    → Apache Cassandra
        ├── Spring Data Neo4j        → Neo4j (Graph DB)
        ├── Spring Data JDBC         → Lightweight JDBC
        └── Spring Data REST         → Exposes repos as REST endpoints

