## Full Request/Response Flow
POST /api/products
Body: { "name": "iPhone 15", "price": 79999, "stock": 100, "category": "ELECTRONICS" }
  1. Controller     receives JSON → validates with @Valid
  2. Service        checks duplicate → builds Product entity
  3. Repository     calls save(product)
  4. Hibernate      generates: INSERT INTO products (name, price, stock, category) VALUES (...)
  5. MySQL          executes INSERT → returns generated id=1
  6. Hibernate      sets product.id = 1
  7. Service        maps Product → ProductResponse DTO
  8. Controller     returns HTTP 201 Created + JSON body

Method      URL                                   Action
POST        /api/products                         Create product
GET         /api/products                         Get all products
GET         /api/products/{id}                    Get by ID
GET         /api/products/search?keyword=         Search by name
GET         /api/products/paged?page=0&size=10    Paginated list
PUT         /api/products/{id}                    Full update
DELETE      /api/products/{id}                    Delete
PATCH       /api/products/{id}/restock?qty=       Restock

Spring Data JPA vs Spring Data MongoDB
Feature             Spring Data JPA                 Spring Data MongoDB
Database Type       Relational (SQL)                NoSQL (Document)
Dependency          spring-boot-starter-data-jpa    spring-boot-starter-data-mongodb
Base Repository     JpaRepository                   MongoRepository
Query Language      JPQL / SQL                      MongoDB Query / Aggregation
Annotation          @Entity, @Table                 @Document, @Field
Schema              Fixed schema                    Flexible/schema-less
Transactions        Full ACID                       Limited (since MongoDB 4.x)
ORM                 Hibernate                       Spring Data MongoDB Converter
